ose nice new floormats we sell at the store, let alone carpets. And then, of course, I’d have to look for another job—and I don’t know anything (wrinkling his face), I have no experience in anything. That means learning all over again. We’d have to live in a damp, shabby little room, saving on food and clothes.”

“Yes, there would be no longer any uncle to help,” said Martha dryly. “No uncle at all.”

“The whole idea is unthinkable,” said Franz.

